Ad Text:
Who We Are 

iSelect and Compare the Market are trusted, well-known brands dedicated to helping millions of Australians compare and buy personal finance and household products such as insurance, energy, and loans. Together, we provide a seamless, customer-focused experience that makes it easier for Australians to find the right products to suit their needs.

What You’ll be doing

As Head of Data Engineering, you will lead the development, scalability, and operational excellence of our core data platforms. You’ll drive best-in-class engineering practices, ensure data integrity and availability, and oversee automation, monitoring, and optimisation of data workflows. You will also shape modern data architectures, implement cloud-based big data solutions, and champion DataOps methodologies to deliver efficient, reliable, and innovative data capabilities.

Define and deliver the data engineering roadmap, ensuring governance, security, and data quality.
Architect, build and optimise scalable data solutions utilising Databricks as our Enterprise Date Platform. 
Implement DataOps practices for automation, CI/CD, and testing.
Build and lead high-performing teams while fostering collaboration and innovation.
Stay ahead of emerging trends and adopt tools to enhance automation and cost efficiency.

What’s in it for you

At Compare the Market and iSelect we offer a dynamic and collaborative work environment where your talents will be recognised and rewarded. You’ll have the opportunity to make a meaningful impact and contribute to our continued success, we also provide:

Vibrant and social community who have annual celebrations, family fun days and regular events.
Enjoy flexible work arrangements, including the option of one day working from home each week or a 9-day fortnight.
Enjoy additional “ME” leave days
Employee discounts on Car, Home, Travel insurance.
Income protection insurance provided to support you in the event of non-work-related illness or injury. 

What Sets You Apart

Demonstrated leadership and team-building skills, with experience managing high-performing engineering teams.
Ability to develop strategy, influence senior stakeholders, and align data solutions with business objectives.
Extensive experience with cloud-based data platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP) and data lake/lakehouse architectures.
Expertise in big data frameworks (Apache Spark, Hadoop, Snowflake, Redshift, BigQuery, Delta Lake) and strong skills in Python, PySpark, SQL.
Proven ability to design and optimise ETL/ELT pipelines for structured and unstructured data.
Hands-on experience with DataOps practices, including CI/CD (Terraform, dbt, GitHub Actions, Azure DevOps) and orchestration tools (Airflow, Dagster, Prefect).
Knowledge of real-time streaming technologies (Kafka, Kinesis, Delta Live Tables).
Strong understanding of data governance, security, and compliance (Unity Catalog, GDPR, CCPA, HIPAA), including RBAC, encryption, and data masking.

Sound like a good fit? Let’s talk.

At Compare the Market and iSelect we’re proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer and we embrace diversity.  

This role is available to candidates with unlimited Australian working rights only. Sponsorship is not available.  

Compare the Market and iSelect are committed to protecting your privacy. All applications and personal information are kept confidential and securely stored in line with Australian privacy laws, used only for recruitment purposes, and not shared with third parties outside the Auto and General Holdings Group without your consent.

We’re seeking a proactive Change Analyst to work across the organisation—partnering with project teams and colleagues—to successfully deliver change projects and agreed business outcomes. With a strong focus on supporting our people through change, you’ll own key change deliverables including engagement planning, understanding impacts, and developing fit‑for‑purpose stakeholder engagement, communications, and training.




Key Responsibilities

In this role, you will:

Apply contemporary, fit‑for‑purpose change methodologies aligned with QTC’s framework, tools and templates, with situational awareness of the change details and impacted groups.

Develop change management artefacts, including (but not limited to) key messages, engagement plans, stakeholder analysis, and change impact assessments.

Build actionable, targeted engagement plans—covering leadership, communications, engagement, training, and recognition.

Conduct analysis, evaluate results, and present findings in a clear, logical, and easy‑to‑understand manner.

Work with project teams to integrate change deliverables and engagement activities into the overall project plan.

Partner with enabling functions (e.g., Internal Communications, People & Development) on engagement activities.

Establish and maintain strong, collaborative relationships with stakeholders to support and embed change.

Communicate effectively and transparently at all levels, ensuring awareness, understanding, and buy‑in of change activities.

Facilitate workshops and deliver training to build capability and readiness.

Act as an enabler of change initiatives, removing barriers and driving adoption.

Perform other duties relevant to project and change management within the scope of the role.




What You’ll Bring

Strong understanding of organisational change management and the drivers of adoption.

Experience working with diverse stakeholders, removing barriers, and progressing complex change initiatives.

Proficient in planning and preparing change communications across varied channels and platforms.

Exceptional written and verbal communication skills.

Skilled in workshop facilitation, training design & delivery, and presenting.

Strong problem-solving skills with the ability to design practical, effective solutions.




Qualifications

Essential

Tertiary qualification in business management, communications, organisational psychology, information technology or a related discipline.

Certification in change management methodologies (e.g., Prosci or equivalent).

Desirable

Certificate in training and development or equivalent learning design credentials.




Experience

Essential

Demonstrated experience delivering organisational and/or technology change, including new technology, processes, and skills.

Proven collaboration and stakeholder engagement capability.

Excellent communication and presentation skills, with the ability to engage both technical and non‑technical audiences.

Ability to operate in a fast‑paced environment with multiple priorities and drive outcomes.

Strong analytical and problem‑solving skills; excellent written and verbal communication.




Build the future with QTC:    

QTC is the central financing authority for the Queensland Government and provides financial resources and services for the State. We manage the State’s funding program in the global capital markets to deliver sustainable and cost-effective borrowings for the Queensland Government, local governments, and other related entities (our clients).    

With a statutory role to advance the financial interests and development of the State, we help to deliver innovative, long-term solutions that contribute to the growth of Queensland’s economy. We protect Queensland’s financial interests and deliver better financial outcomes by centralising the management of our clients’ borrowings, cash investments, and foreign exchange.    

We do work that improves Queensland for generations. We are a leader in finance, creating meaningful solutions with profound outcomes. We set the standard in financial solutions. We address the challenges of today, with results for tomorrow.    

AT QTC we celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. We have an equitable, barrier-free application process so please inform us of any accessibility requirements in your application or you can reach out to our Talent Team careers@qtc.com.au.

Job Title: Senior Machine Learning Engineer - Evaluations (Design Generation)
Ad Text:
Company Description


Join the team redefining how the world experiences design.

Hey, g'day, mabuhay, kia ora,你好, hallo, vítejte!

Thanks for stopping by. We know job hunting can be a little time consuming and you're probably keen to find out what's on offer, so we'll get straight to the point. 

Where and how you can work

Our flagship campus is in Sydney, with a second campus in Melbourne and co-working spaces in Brisbane, Perth, Adelaide, and Auckland, NZ. You have flexibility in how and where you work — whether that's from one of our spaces, from home, or a mix of both. This role is remote-friendly within Australia or New Zealand, so you can choose the setup that empowers you and your team to do your best work.

Job Description


About the team:
 

Canva's Design Generation systems use AI to create complete designs from text descriptions - turning user intent into layouts, images, typography, and color palettes. At scale, we generate millions of designs monthly, making reliable quality evaluation critical. The Design Generation Platform team (8 engineers) supports Design Generation infrastructure with focus on developer experience tooling, platform orchestration, and self-service capabilities. We own the plumbing that makes Design Generation systems observable, debuggable, and improvable.

Our philosophy: Platform owns orchestration, not application logic. We build reusable infrastructure that scales across Design Generation rather than solving one-off problems. We emphasize collaborative decision-making, evidence-based approaches, and building capabilities that serve researchers and engineers across Design Generation.

About the role:

As the Design Generation Evaluation owner, you'll build the infrastructure that enables quality monitoring across Design Generation. You're the expert who both understands evaluation methodologies deeply AND builds the infrastructure to scale them across the organization.

This role sits at the intersection of three critical areas:

Evaluation Strategy & Expertise: You'll guide Design Generation teams on how to evaluate their systems effectively - which methods work for different scenarios, how to set up robust test sets, when to use LLM-as-Judge vs. 1st Party Quality Models vs. user signals, and how to balance cost with detection speed. You'll establish evaluation best practices and patterns that teams can adopt.

Infrastructure & Scale: You'll build the platforms that make evaluation accessible and automated - alerting systems, continuous monitoring, production sampling, step-level harnesses. Your goal is enabling teams to run evaluations effortlessly, eventually integrating evaluation checks into Continuous Deployment so quality gates happen automatically.

Ecosystem Integration: Canva has multiple evaluation tools. You'll articulate how these pieces fit together for Design Generation, define clear integration points, and build the connective tissue that makes the evaluation story coherent rather than fragmented.

The challenge: Quality degradation in generative systems is subtle. Designs look slightly off-brand, layouts don't quite work, users stop publishing without clear signals. You'll need deep ML intuition to build detection systems that catch real issues while minimizing false positives. This role requires navigating ambiguity, making pragmatic architecture decisions, and building infrastructure that serves diverse evaluation needs across research and engineering.

What you’ll do (responsibilities)

Understand and optimize existing evaluation systems including LLM-as-Judge frameworks, visual quality models , and multi-dimensional scoring approaches - analyzing their strengths, limitations, and trade-offs to identify gaps in coverage and opportunities for improvement across brand adherence, visual appeal, layout quality, and functional correctness

Design and implement automated evaluation pipelines that score generated designs at scale, balancing accuracy with computational cost

Define evaluation strategies for different scenarios: pre-deployment validation, continuous monitoring, A/B experiment analysis, and model comparison

Curate high-quality evaluation datasets and benchmark suites that represent diverse use cases, edge cases, and quality dimensions

Integrate evaluation systems into continuous deployment pipelines, creating automated quality gates that catch regressions before production

Reduce evaluation cycle time to enable teams to iterate faster on model improvements and launch experiments earlier

Partner with research teams to understand evaluation needs for new model architectures and capabilities

Define the evaluation ecosystem strategy: how different evaluation tools and methods compose together for Design Generation

Guide teams on evaluation best practices, appropriate methodologies for their use cases, and interpretation of results

What we're looking for

Strong ML engineering fundamentals with experience building and maintaining production ML systems at scale

Proven ability to build robust, scalable infrastructure (not just models) - you're a platform engineer who speaks ML

Deep understanding of distributed systems, observability patterns, and monitoring best practices

Python proficiency with production-quality coding standards, code reviews, and testing practices

Experience with data pipelines, time-series data, and statistical analysis for detecting anomalies

SQL fluency for querying and analyzing large datasets across data warehouse and analytics systems

Track record of building self-service platforms or developer tooling that gets adoption

Excellent collaboration skills - this role requires working across teams to understand needs and deliver solutions

Experience with evaluation of Gen AI systems at scale (even better if that’s evaluation of systems with creative outputs!)

Additional Information


Don't tick all the boxes? Don't worry about that - nobody does!  We’d still love to hear from you! At Canva, we know that great engineers come from a variety of backgrounds, and we value passion, curiosity, and a willingness to learn just as much as specific experience. If you're excited about this role but don’t tick every box, we encourage you to apply, you might a great fit in ways you didn’t expect!

What's in it for you?

Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard - and we do - but you'll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity and fun woven throughout life at Canva, too. We also offer a stack of benefits to set you up for every success in and outside of work.

Here's a taste of what's on offer:

Equity packages - we want our success to be yours too
Inclusive parental leave policy that supports all parents & carers
An annual Vibe & Thrive allowance to support your wellbeing, social connection, office setup & more
Flexible leave options that empower you to be a force for good, take time to recharge and supports you personally

Check out  lifeatcanva.com  for more info.

Other stuff to know

We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills and passion, as well as how you can enhance Canva and our culture. When you apply, please tell us the pronouns you use and any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.

At AustralianSuper, we truly care about our colleagues.​ We know work and life are intertwined. That's why we support the diverse needs of everyone and have policies that enable us all to thrive and be truly flexible. We ensure diversity is celebrated for the opportunity it provides us all to learn and grow and deliver better outcomes for members.

Your New Role

Reporting to the Business Analysis Manager, the focus of your new role involves working closely with the business initiative owners, internal subject matter experts, tech partners and other stakeholders to elicit relevant information in order to define and document business requirements, perform analysis, provide advice and support the delivery of projects/initiatives undertaken by Member Experience department. The prime areas of focus for the role are changes and projects related to digital platforms, customer platforms & analytics and other related digital initiatives.

Key duties include but are not limited to:

Conduct high level business analysis, defining and documenting business, information and process requirements. Elicits project requirements using various methods, including but not limited to interviews, document reviews, requirements workshops, surveys, researching and resolving issues
Identify and define the information, business and process requirements for specified initiatives collaborating with applicable stakeholders
Coordinate and run internal and external stakeholder workshops to facilitate requirements gathering and or configuration requirements
Critically evaluates business solution information and customer data requirements, reconciles conflicts, decomposes high level information into details and identifies existing, new and external data sourcing needs.
Document details to participate & contribute to PI planning sessions
Engage in scrum events, assisting with planning, backlog refinement and ordering, requirements comprehension and delivery improvements
Ensure relevant legislative and organisational requirements are met including maintaining a thorough understanding of changes to relevant regulations
Ensure appropriate and relevant governance structures, policies and processes are followed, and advocate for continuous improvement to these

What You'll Need

Experience as a business analyst working on successful delivery of significant projects / initiatives
Proven ability to successfully gather requirements and get results with minimal supervision
Understanding of how to interpret business needs and translate these into operational requirements
Demonstrated ability to write clearly and succinctly and present complex analysis in accessible formats; experience with digital / agile methods including user stories etc
Ability to synthesise member preferences, regulatory requirements and the Fund's strategic ambitions to identify workable and measurable solutions with a member experience lens
Knowledge of various digital platforms that can drive better customer interactions
Strong interpersonal skills with proven ability to build and maintain strong relationships with key stakeholders
Excellent verbal skills and the ability to interact professionally and influence a diverse group, executives, managers and subject matter experts

Life at AustralianSuper

AustralianSuper is committed to colleague development, and we support our people with ongoing learning, coaching and training, as well as career opportunities across our expanding global organisation. We offer generous leave entitlements and promote a blended working environment in which all roles can flex, and we're happy to discuss what this looks like for you.

We cultivate a workplace that champions safety, respect, inclusiveness and diversity. We are committed to supporting our diverse workforce in a way that is inclusive and embraces diversity in all its forms. If you require any reasonable adjustments to the recruitment process or the role, please let our recruitment team know.

What's Next

Apply now, if you share our values of Energy, Integrity, Generosity of Spirit and Excellent Outcomes and would like the opportunity to work in a challenging, growing and rapidly evolving team to deliver outstanding results.

Progress powered by purpose.

Slalom

Slalom is a purpose-driven consulting company focused on strategy, technology, and business transformation. Founded in 2001, we had a simple goal - build a company where people love their work and love their life. ​As we continue to grow in Australia, we have a responsibility and opportunity to do good in the world. We’re committed to building our business in ways that are sustainable and responsible, while creating innovative solutions to the world’s biggest challenges. We have bold aspirations for the future and together with our people, partners, and customers, we take measurable actions for today.

The Strategy team

 Slalom's Strategy team helps our clients re-imagine what's possible, when making the most of technology and modern ways of working. As a Strategy Consultant, you will lead from the front, working in both team-based projects, interacting with clients, assisting with pre-sales pursuits, and providing mentoring to more junior consultants.

The Role: Strategist & Value Architect – Principal

 We’re looking for someone who has truly lived and breathed business casing: someone who has led it, delivered value, and understands it not just from a business strategy perspective, but also from a technology strategy lens. The right person will be capable of taking a business case and using it as a foundation to drive action. Ideally, they’ve done this before across projects, initiatives, ROI analysis, and more. The role also involves value architecture: connecting strategy all the way through to initiatives. It’s about tying everything together: vision, mission, values, and execution.

What You Will Do

In this role, you'll work with your colleagues in Strategy and in other capability teams to help shape work, sell it, and execute it, all in a client-facing capacity. Our team is invigorated by new challenges and aren’t shy to seek out new learning opportunities or challenge the status quo. We need someone who’s a subject matter expert and can also guide and upskill others in the team in how to develop strong business cases.

Meeting with client stakeholders to understand and define financial models that support a compelling business case
Conducting strategic and financial analyses, and incorporating into a compelling and substantiated narrative that influences executive decisions to take action
Identifying, communicating and modelling benefits and business value, for an executive audience
Lead or contribute to platform and product evaluations, RFPs, M&A recommendations, business case design, strategy formulation, roadmap development, and technology landscape assessments.
Lead or contribute through all phases of the customer development lifecycle, including stakeholder relationship management, pre-sales, project alignment, and engagement delivery.
Lead or contribute to the design and implementation of technology operating models, supporting e.g. Digital Transformation, Cloud Adoption, DevOps enablement, and AI enablement.

What You'll Bring To Slalom

Experience working across multiple businesses, business and technology domains, and industries.
Broad understanding of key and emerging technologies, including how they interact and the value they offer.
Clear understanding of the technology landscape and architecture as it pertains to business systems, from customer-facing applications to legacy systems.
Ability to develop and implement effective technology strategies aligned with business objectives.
Experience with various architectures, technical solutions, delivery and operating models and their organizational impacts, including alignment of business goals, guiding principles, governance, vendor relationships, and funding approaches.
Ability to establish credibility with customers and partners from initial meetings onward.
Passion for driving effective collaboration with customer stakeholders, partners, and cross-functional Slalom teams.

Our Values

Our culture and values reflect each individual Slalomer. We are dedicated to encouraging workplace diversity and ensuring all our people, from any background can contribute to their full potential. We wish to build a team that echoes the diversity of the communities we serve, and our values are an active part of our every-day, guiding our decisions.

What keeps us here?

When we moved to Australia in 2020, we had no idea just how important our work/life balance would need to be. We’ve asked our consultants what makes Slalom a great place to work and the most common answer – “the freedom to be ourselves when life gets in the way”. We make a big effort to bring everyone together and allow space when space is needed. We believe in helping each other thrive in work and life and are proud to invest in benefits that include holistic wellbeing, meaningful allowances, and investment in our team’s professional, technical, and personal growth.

Slalom is an equal opportunity employer and welcomes all qualified applicants. Slalom does not discriminate on grounds of race, religion, or belief, ethnic or national origin, disability, age, marital, domestic, or civil partnership status, sexual orientation, gender identity, or any other basis as protected by applicable law.

Ad Text:
Company Description

Where can a career at KPMG Audit take you? KPMG is the audit firm of the future. We provide an environment for Innovation, Impact and Opportunity. 

You're joining an organisation where people are firmly at the heart of everything we do, and your success if just as important as ours. You'll get the opportunity to take audit to new levels using new technology, including AI and where you redefine the value of audit and leverage automation to focus on work that matters most to you and to clients. We offer meaningful work that has a broad reaching and positive impact on our people, our clients, financial markets and the Australian economy. With a focus on adaptability, we're transforming the audit experience for our clients and our people. 

But you'll also have access to unrivalled career opportunities, where you can tap into a global network of experts, that will help you grow your career. 

KPMG is a place where you can come as you are, learn for a lifetime and be part of a global community where you will thrive. 

Job Description

KPMG Mid Market & Private is a specialist division of KPMG Australia, dedicated to advising the emerging, private and mid-market. We work with established and emerging entrepreneurs, family businesses, private clients, not-for-profits and fast-growing companies to build successful, efficient and resilient organisations. By bringing our diverse expertise together, we give our clients the confidence to focus on the things that will truly make an impact and help them grow.

Our Audit teams provide value to our clients by delivering specialised quality audit and assurance services. High-quality, independent financial statement audits are essential to maintaining investor confidence. Our audit professionals are committed to the public interest, challenging assumptions, and unlocking valuable insights based on a solid understanding of an organisation’s business and industry.

Your Opportunity

As a Senior Analyst in our Darwin Audit & Assurance team, you will: 

Provide audit operational support on engagements with a focus on preparation, delivery, reporting and evaluation of the audit results in response to the needs of stakeholders and external regulators. 

Provide inspirational and engaging coaching and mentorship to junior team members 

Develop strong relationships with our prestigious audit clients and play a key role in the delivery of quality assurance and reporting

How are you extraordinary?

You like to be proud of the work you produce and are accountable and committed to owning high-profile projects.

You enjoy working in the details, with a proactive attitude towards accuracy and deadlines.

You actively seek out opportunities for growth, are comfortable challenging the status quo, and enjoy getting out of your comfort zone.

Your Experience

At KPMG, we believe diversity of thought, background and experience strengthens relationships and delivers meaningful benefits to our people, our clients, and communities. To be considered for this opportunity, your qualifications, skills & experience could include:

Bring a proven track record of high performance and success

Have gained strong IFRS skills

Exceptional problem solving and analytical skills

Highly developed written and verbal communication skills

Demonstrated team leadership abilities.

Qualifications

We are looking for applicants that have relevant tertiary qualifications including a CA, or ability to obtain a CA.

Additional Information

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

Job Title: Senior Change Manager – Microsoft 365 Copilot Rollout
Ad Text:
Senior Change Manager – Microsoft 365 Copilot Rollout

Brisbane | 6 Month Fixed- Term Contract with potential extension

Role Overview

We're on the lookout for a seasoned Change Manager to guide our end client through a pivotal Microsoft 365 Copilot transformation. This six-month contract role with potential extension is dedicated to fostering user adoption, managing stakeholder relations, and ensuring a smooth rollout of M365 Copilot solutions across the business.

You'll collaborate with IT, business leaders, and end-users to design and deliver robust change management strategies, ensuring minimal disruption while driving maximum benefits. This position calls for a professional who’s adept at both the technical side of M365/Copilot deployments and the people aspects of technology change.

Main Responsibilities

Change Strategy & Planning
Craft and execute comprehensive change management plans for M365 Copilot rollouts
Conduct impact assessments to pinpoint affected groups and outline change needs
Develop tailored communication and training strategies for various user segments
Define and track success metrics and KPIs to gauge adoption and change impact

Stakeholder Engagement

Build strong partnerships with business leaders, IT, and other key stakeholders
Facilitate workshops and focus groups to capture requirements and address concerns
Manage resistance and enhance buy-in at all organisational levels
Deliver regular updates and reports to leadership and project teams

Training & Enablement

Design and deliver training initiatives to boost user confidence and capability in M365 Copilot
Create user guides, quick references, and self-help resources
Identify and train power users and change champions for grassroots support
Evaluate training effectiveness and adapt strategies based on feedback

Communication & Support

Develop and share targeted communications to inform and motivate users throughout the change journey
Handle change-related queries and resolve escalations during rollout
Work with technical teams to ensure robust support mechanisms are in place
Celebrate quick wins and share success stories to sustain engagement

Required Experience & Skills

Change Management Expertise
At least 5 – 10 years in change management, ideally within technology-driven projects
Proven background leading successful change initiatives in medium to large settings
Formal change management certification (e.g., Prosci, ACMP, CCMP) is highly regarded.
Familiarity with structured change methodologies and frameworks

M365 & Copilot Proficiency

Hands-on experience with Microsoft 365 rollouts, migrations, or optimisation efforts
Direct involvement in deploying Microsoft Copilot for M365 or similar AI solutions
Strong grasp of the M365 suite (Teams, SharePoint, OneDrive, Outlook, etc.)
Awareness of AI adoption challenges and best practices for enterprise AI tool uptake
Professional Attributes
Excellent stakeholder engagement and influencing abilities across all levels
Outstanding written and spoken communication, with a knack for simplifying the complex
Experience in developing training content and delivering engaging presentations
Ability to work autonomously while collaborating effectively across teams
Proficiency in project management and change management platforms

Key Competencies

Adaptability – Agile in refining strategies to reflect feedback and shifting priorities
Analytical Thinking – Skilled at evaluating situations, identifying risks, and crafting data-driven solutions
Emotional Intelligence – Attuned to the human aspects of change and able to respond with empathy
Results Orientation – Committed to delivering measurable outcomes and achieving adoption goals
Strategic Mindset – Capable of aligning change activities with overarching business objectives
Collaboration – A true team player, adept at building productive relationships across diverse groups

What We Value

We’re after a change specialist who blends technical acumen with superb interpersonal skills. You’ll thrive in a fast-paced setting, manage competing priorities with ease, and genuinely enjoy supporting people through change.

The ideal candidate will demonstrate:

A practical, solution-oriented mindset for overcoming adoption challenges
Energy and enthusiasm that encourages others to embrace new approaches
A keen interest in AI technologies and their potential to transform work
Credibility with both technical and non-technical stakeholders
A history of empowering organisations to better handle future change
Immediate or near-immediate availability for this six-month assignment

If you’re passionate about driving organisational transformation and have the right M365 and Copilot expertise, we’d be thrilled to connect with you.

About the role 
Ventia’s Finance team require a full-time SAP Security and Risk Senior Analyst to join the team.


This role reports to the SAP Security Assurance Manager and is responsible to ensure SAP security, roles and risks and governance are managed effectively.


This role is based out of Cremorne, VIC, but open to any applicants for any of the major states.


What you’ll be doing: 

Manage role and access requests for Ventia’s SAP landscape including SAP ECC and BTP
Manage stakeholders from IT, business areas and external service providers to provide solutions and obtain resolutions in a timely manner
Daily reporting of Segregation of Duties and Sensitive Transactions risks and mitigating controls
Analyse and remediate SOD and Sensitive Access risks and improve role management processes
Maintain Ventia’s GRC solution – Soterion for ruleset and mitigating control updates
Identify and implement solutions to uplift Ventia’s risk and control environment based on risk frameworks, best practice and experience

About you 
The successful applicant will have worked in a similar position ideally within a large organisation in the infrastructure industry accompanied with:


Business Process specific SOD and Sensitive Transaction knowledge and remediation experience
Strong analytical skills to analyse information across different applications to draw insights and actions
Project execution experience to manage end-to-end change management, including ability to develop multiple options to resolve a problem
Internal / external audit and risk management
In-depth understanding of core Cybersecurity concepts that relate to Identity and Access Management, SAP and ERP applications specific Identity and GRC processes
Security and Identity Access Management fluent


Diversity
Ventia is enriched by the diverse experiences, talents and cultures that our people bring to the organisation, while celebrating and respecting the communities we operate in. We are committed to providing a safe and positive environment that provides equal opportunities for individuals of all backgrounds, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, Māori and Pasifika people, LGTBQI+, Women, Veterans and spouses and people with disabilities.


What We Offer You
Not only do we offer a competitive salary and career growth, we have also partnered with some reputable organisations to be able to offer discounts on Health Insurance, Banking (new home loans, credit cards, everyday bank accounts), flights & accommodation, car hire, car leasing and much more.


How to apply

Select "Apply Now" to submit your application.

Job Title: Manager - Business Partnering & Analysis | Growing Global Leader
Ad Text:
Ref: A000909

High-Impact Analysis
Key Stakeholder Leadership
Direct impact on projects

The Company

Robert Half Executive Search (RH ES) has been retained to appoint a commercially savvy and hands-on Manager - Business Partnering & Analysis with a well-respected, market leading manufacturing technology business.

With operations and solutions serving markets across Australia, New Zealand, and South East Asia, the business is renowned for its technical expertise, product quality, and commitment to innovation, design, manufacture, and distribution of highly engineered solutions.

The Role

Reporting to the Regional Finance Director, your focus will be on delivering financial insight, business analysis and decision support to support improved profitability, productivity and business improvement initiatives.

You will be the primary link between Finance and the broader business, working closely with Manufacturing, Operations, Sales, Marketing, to optimise business performance and ensure the business continues to apply best practice.

Key Responsibilities & Focus Areas

As the Manager - Business Partnering & Analysis, you will provide financial insight and technical expertise to guide decision-making, reporting directly to the Finance Director and acting as a critical resource to all ASEAN businesses.

High-Impact Analysis & Performance Management:
Analyse variances, trends, and KPIs to monitor financial and operational performance across the transactional landscape.
Develop and refine financial models to improve accuracy and insight.
Help drive accountability for performance across business units through clear reporting.
Strategic Finance & Decision Support:
Provide financial insight and modelling to support strategic choices and investment decisions.
Translate complex financial data into clear, actionable recommendations for senior leaders.
Expert Use of Excel & Financial Systems:
Utilise expert-level Excel skills to design and deliver innovative financial/commercial analysis, including budget management, forecasting, and on-demand planning.
Implement improvements to financial systems, models, and tools to increase efficiency and reliability.
Exceptional Stakeholder Engagement & Business Partnering:
Build strong relationships with operational and functional leaders, providing proactive financial guidance.
Act as a constructive challenger, supporting robust, data-driven decision-making.
Present complex insights clearly to non-financial stakeholders, tailoring communication to the audience. Your key stakeholders will include the Leadership Team and Business Unit/Operations Managers.
Leadership & Team Development:
Provide day-to-day leadership, guidance, and oversight to a team of primarily Management Accountants (direct reports).
Review and ensure accuracy, completeness, and quality of financial outputs.

What You Will Bring:

Tertiary Qualifications in Finance or Commerce disciplines.
CA/CPA or business qualification
Highly competent to lead, design, and deliver innovative financial/commercial analysis.

Job Title: General Manager - Client success & Research Transformation
Ad Text:
Endpoint IQ is a Brisbane-based SaaS company working with universities, research institutes, and health services across Australia, New Zealand, and overseas. Our platforms streamline the end‑to‑end research management pipeline, so researchers spend less time on admin and more time on impact.

We’re looking for a solutions‑focused, personable leader for our Client Success and Implementation team. We’re a medium‑sized, specialist team with low ego, a collaborative style, and close relationships with our clients. With the pace of change across higher education, this role is ideal for someone who wants to help shape the next generation of research management systems while staying connected to the sector.

You will:

Lead a multidisciplinary team of project managers and product specialists (~12FTE) delivering multiple concurrent implementations (10–24 month programmes)

Bring research management expertise to challenge "lift and shift" processes and design better ways of working for our clients

Own our implementation framework and delivery standards across institutions in Australia and overseas

Ensure Level 2 application support and product-specialist knowledge flow cleanly through to our developers and support engineers

Support Sales with research-literate input to proposals and take part in pre-sales demos for new and upsell opportunities.

About you

You understand the research management ecosystem and how universities and health services actually get work done. You may have come up through a Research Office, Ethics and Governance, Grants, or Graduate Research, or you may have led delivery or support for research‑adjacent software. What matters most is practical experience helping researchers and professional staff navigate processes such as ethics review, grants and contracts, HDR candidature, or post‑award finance, and turning that understanding into reliable delivery, clear communication, and measurable outcomes.

You’ve worked across multiple stakeholder groups and are comfortable balancing day‑to‑day matters with the dynamics of multiple streams of project delivery. Whether your path has been operational within a research intensive organisation or product/delivery for a vendor you will bring credibility with research management professionals and the judgement to lead a team that’s close to clients and outcomes.

What you’ll bring

Meaningful experience in research management or a closely related domain, with fluency in processes like ethics/governance, grants and contracts, HDR/GR, or post‑award.

A track record delivering or supporting business systems, ideally SaaS.

Strength in stakeholder engagement across academic, professional, and IT groups, with clear, plain‑language communication.

Comfort moving between detail and big picture: from root‑cause analysis and SOPs to roadmap, prioritisation, and acceptance.

Team leadership that’s low‑ego, collaborative, and oriented to service quality and measurable client outcomes.

Why join Endpoint IQ

Stay adjacent to higher education and research while broadening into the tech sector

Work with multiple large orgnisations and see your ideas postitively influence practice across the sector

Join a supportive, close-knit team where your voice matters and bureaucracy is light

Work based in Toowong, with practical flexibility and occasional travel to clients and overseas conferences

Real opportunity to shape how research is managed during a time of major change in the sector.

Together building prosperity in the Kimberley and beyond — Safety, Sustainability, Community: it’s in our DNA.
 
At KMS, success is not just what we do — it’s how we do it. We’re seeking a hands on, outcomes focused Principal Continuous Improvement to embed a culture of improvement and lift performance across the business. You’ll be a trusted advisor to senior leaders and own enterprise level programs that strengthen governance, sustainability and stakeholder confidence.
 
About the Project

Kimberley Mineral Sands Pty Ltd (KMS) is a 50/50 joint venture between Sheffield Resources Limited and YGH Australia Investment Pty Ltd (Yansteel). The Thunderbird Mineral Sands Operation (Thunderbird) is located mid-way between Derby and Broome, in the Kimberley region of Western Australia. 

Thunderbird is one of the largest and highest-grade zircon mineral sands deposits in the world and contains valuable heavy minerals including ilmenite, zircon, leucoxene, and rutile, which are extracted and exported via the Port of Broome. 

Our head office is based in Broome, and together we are focused on delivering economic and social benefits for the West Kimberley and its communities. We do this through living our values of Integrity, Accountability, Humility, Co-Creation and Inclusivity. 



About the Role

Location: Perth or Broome (Monday–Friday corporate roster) with regular travel to the Thunderbird site
Department: Commercial & Finance
Reports to: Head of Commercial
 

What you’ll lead

Enterprise Continuous Improvement (CI) framework: design, implement and monitor a practical improvement framework aligned to organisational strategy; track outcomes and benefits with clear reporting.
Stewardship (organisational “wiring”) Program: own the design, governance and activities cadence (balanced scorecards, dashboards, KPIs) to drive accountability, transparency and responsible resource management.
Priority improvement delivery: identify and prioritise opportunities; facilitate CI activities such as value stream mapping, problem solving and idea generation; lead compliant process enhancements and sustainment plans.
Culture & capability: coach and mentor leaders and teams in CI methods (Lean, Six Sigma); develop tools, templates and training that build capability.

Your critical thinking, analytical capability, and process expertise will help align stakeholders, streamline operations, and elevate organisational performance. You will provide process leadership and guidance to our process roles, across squads and business units, all with the goal of driving strategic outcomes, enhancing member experiences, and improving stakeholder satisfaction. 

The core accountabilities of the role will include: 

Deliver strategic guidance across the full lifecycle of process management and continuous improvement, ensuring alignment with AP+’s strategic objectives and operational priorities.

Lead and facilitate workshops to confirm process ownership, clarify roles and responsibilities, and ensure alignment across stakeholders. Document agreements & directions that support the assessment of organisational process maturity, and translate insights into actionable, prioritised roadmaps that drive meaningful and sustainable improvement. 
Design and embed experience-led processes that create clarity, consistency, and measurable outcomes across the organisation. Use insights from stakeholder and employee experience to shape process expectations, define aligned ways of working, and ensure processes support seamless, high-quality interactions. Partner with process owners to translate desired experiences into practical, scalable process designs, establish clear responsibilities, and create mechanisms that enable continuous learning, accountability, and ongoing improvement. 
Partner with cross-functional teams to identify inefficiencies, uncover automation opportunities, and maintain a prioritised backlog of process improvement initiatives. 
Develop clear and compelling reports, insights, and executive-ready presentations that articulate improvement outcomes, performance metrics, and progress updates. 
Promote a culture of process excellence, best practice adoption, and ongoing innovation across the organisation. 
Develop and embed sustainable knowledge practices, aligning policies, procedures, and work instructions to empower employees and strengthen operational effectiveness. 

The capabilities needed to be successful for this role are: 

10+ years of progressively senior experience in business process management, improvement, optimisation, or process engineering, at scale, using enterprise toolsets. 
Proven success in leading process improvement workshops, enabling cross-functional collaboration, designing end-to-end processes, and delivering initiatives that drive significant operational or strategic impact. 
Ability to influence and drive change in complex environments, building a culture of continuous improvement and strong stakeholder engagement. 
Familiarity with project management methodologies and tools, with the capability to partner with delivery teams to coordinate change across the organisation. 
Working knowledge of frameworks such as APQC, ITIL, and COBIT, and how they are applied to strengthen organisational process maturity and governance. 
Experience in benchmarking, developing performance measures, and leveraging data-driven insights to improve process performance. 
Understanding of delivery practices including RAID, estimation approaches, and structured reporting to enable strong process oversight and governance.
Advanced training or certification in process improvement or change methodologies (e.g., Black or Green Belt Six Sigma) is highly advantageous. 

What happens next: 

At AP+, we believe in the power of passion, pride, and purpose. Our team is united by a mission to transform Australia’s payments landscape, and we work together with dedication and ambition.

About the team


The Strategic Data Science team provides Airwallex’s Leadership with the data, tooling, and insights needed to amplify Airwallex’s rapid growth. We partner across the entire business, giving us an overarching view and opinion on what Airwallex should prioritize. Our expertise spans the full data stack, and we use it to tackle complex data problems that will shape the future of global fintech. The team is growing quickly, and currently resides in the US, China, and Singapore. Learn more about the data science team in this blog.

This role is based in Melbourne.

Responsibilities:


Be the go-to data partner for the Head of ANZ

Partner with Sales, Marketing, Finance, Data Engineering, and Product to align metric definitions/dimensions and data sources across the business

Leverage AI to generate insights and improve business and team efficiency

Support Airwallex’s forecasting efforts by applying advanced statistical methods

Scope and build data products. In some cases MVPs, and in others, fully fleshed out solutions

Foster an environment grounded in technical excellence, clear communication, and proactive critical thinking

Who you are


We’re looking for people who meet the minimum qualifications for this role. The preferred qualifications are great to have, but are not mandatory.

Minimum qualifications:


5+ years industry experience and a degree in a quantitative field (e.g. Statistics, Engineering, Sciences, Computer Science, Economics)

Excellent communication skills, ideally with a proven track record of working directly with executive-level stakeholders to influence strategy

Expertise in forecasting

Expertise in data querying languages (e.g. SQL) and scripting languages (e.g. Python, R)

Experience with data architecture technologies such as Airflow, Databricks, and dbt

Preferred qualifications:


Experience in technology, financial services and/or a high growth environment

Experience with Excel and Finance systems (e.g. Oracle)

All official communication will come from an @airwallex.com email address. Please apply only through careers.airwallex.com or our official LinkedIn page.

Airwallex does not accept unsolicited resumes from search firms/recruiters. Search firms/recruiters submitting resumes to Airwallex on an unsolicited basis shall be deemed to accept this condition, regardless of any other provision to the contrary.
